---
import BaseLayout from "../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Affiliate Disclosure"
  description="How Australian Home Collective will disclose approved affiliate links while maintaining editorial independence and reader choice."
>
  <header class="page-intro">
    <div class="narrow">
      <p class="eyebrow">Disclosure</p>
      <h1>Affiliate Disclosure</h1>
      <p class="lead">
        Australian Home Collective does not currently publish affiliate links. If that changes,
        qualifying links will be clearly disclosed and used only through an approved process.
      </p>
    </div>
  </header>
  <section class="content narrow">
    <p>
      Future affiliate links may help support the publication. A commission may be earned at no
      extra cost to the reader when someone buys through a qualifying link.
    </p>

    <h2>How this affects guides</h2>
    <p>
      Commercial relationships will not determine the topics we cover or the conclusions we
      reach. Reader trust takes priority over short-term revenue.
    </p>
    <p>
      Named products, retailer links and affiliate links require editorial and commercial
      approval before publication. An approved link will not replace the measurements,
      suitability checks and limitations readers need to make their own decision.
    </p>

    <h2>Reader choice</h2>
    <p>
      You are never required to use our links. Before buying, check the retailer's current
      product information, price, delivery details, returns policy and suitability for your
      household.
    </p>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
